      "title": "GenAsset img2img workflow notes",
      "properties": {},
      "widgets_values": [
        "# GenAsset asset-browser img2img re-edit\n\nThis is the full GenAsset round trip.\n\n1. `Load Asset From GenAsset` loads the current version by asset name or exact asset id.\n2. The loaded image goes into `VAE Encode`; this replaces the empty latent used in txt2img.\n3. `KSampler` runs img2img with `denoise = 0.55` so the prompt can relocate or restyle the asset while preserving structure.\n4. `Save To GenAsset` saves the edited image back as the next version.\n\nPaste your workspace token into both GenAsset nodes. Use the asset page's **Copy asset id** or the asset name for `asset_query`. Use the same asset name in `Save To GenAsset` when you want a new version on the same asset. The saved workflow JSON redacts workspace tokens automatically and the black-image guard prevents blank runs from becoming versions."
      ]
    }
